FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

The Cherry Point Refinery has an excellent record of accident prevention over the past 24 years, 1999 through 2023. The frequency of accidental releases has been extremely low. The refinery has not had any release that has gone outside of the refinery boundaries. There have not been any OSHA recordable injuries resulting from a flammable release or a toxic release in the past five years. Every incident is investigated carefully and changes are instituted to prevent such an incident from happening again.

