ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND RESPONSE POLICIES

The BP Cherry Point Refinery has a long standing commitment to worker and public safety. Resources invested in accident prevention-such as personnel training and safety consideration in the design, installation, operation, and maintenance of the processes-demonstrate this commitment. The BP Cherry Point's Environmental Policy states that The Cherry Point Refinery recognizes and is committed to the protection and respect of the environment within which the refinery operates. [The Refinery] shall operate in such a manner as to minimize the refinery's impact on the environment while competitively producing quality petroleum products for market. The Cherry Point Refinery's Environmental Policy is as follows:

Pursue the goal of no damage to the environment;

Commit to continuously improve the Local Operating Management System (LOMS) Manual to enhance performance and continually drive down the environmental impact of operations by reducing waste, emissions and discharges, and using energy efficiently;

Comply with all relevant environmental laws, regulations, and other environmental initiatives in which the refinery subscribes;

Support pollution prevention within the refinery through the procedures and activities identified within our pollution prevention plan;

Ensure that every employee is familiar with the refinery's environmental policy and encourage continued commitment to its intent;

Consult with, listen to, and respond openly to our customers, employees, neighbors, public interest groups and those who work with us;

Work with others-our partners, suppliers, competitors and regulators-to raise the standard of our industry;

Recognize those who contribute to improved environmental performance; and

Develop environmental objectives and targets.


